1
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
[birds chirping]

2
00:01:42,708 --> 00:01:45,375
-[soup boiling]
-[COWGIRL humming cheerily]

3
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:50,458
[sips]

4
00:01:50,541 --> 00:01:52,000
Oh. Huh?

5
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:53,708
Good morning!

6
00:01:53,791 --> 00:01:57,375
It'll be just a minute.
Breakfast is almost ready.

7
00:01:57,458 --> 00:02:00,250
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Run.
-Huh?

8
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:02,291
Okay. You're kidding.

9
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:05,500
You are, right?
Come on.

10
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:07,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
There were tracks.

11
00:02:07,791 --> 00:02:09,791
♪

12
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:15,208
Goblins.

13
00:02:15,291 --> 00:02:17,750
All right, so you'll
just fight them off, then.

14
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:20,791
-Won't you?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] I can't.

15
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:23,291
[gasps]

16
00:02:23,375 --> 00:02:26,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER] In a cave,
I would win against them,

17
00:02:26,791 --> 00:02:29,750
even if their numbers
were a hundred strong.

18
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:32,416
No matter what,
I'd be victorious.

19
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:35,708
But...

20
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:39,333
there were at least
ten sets of scout footprints,

21
00:02:39,416 --> 00:02:42,541
which means this horde
definitely has a leader.

22
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:49,416
Not a hob or a shaman, no.

23
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,666
Judging from their numbers,
it must be...

24
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:58,083
something much stronger.

25
00:02:58,166 --> 00:03:00,750
A Goblin Lord.

26
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:03,291
[soup boiling, sizzling]

27
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:06,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER] The attack
will come tonight or tomorrow.

28
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,375
We don't have time
to ask the military for help.

29
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:10,750
Based on the tracks,

30
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:13,208
it's a horde of more
than a hundred goblins.

31
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:16,458
[COWGIRL]
So many. That's terrifying.

32
00:03:17,583 --> 00:03:21,458
But why here? Why the farm?
What do they want with it?

33
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,875
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Most likely
they'd use it as a stronghold

34
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:26,958
to launch an attack on the town.

35
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,750
I'm not a platinum-ranked
adventurer.

36
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,583
I'm not a hero.

37
00:03:33,666 --> 00:03:37,083
I don't see how we can
possibly muster enough people

38
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:40,000
to face more than a hundred
monsters in an open field.

39
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:44,041
I'm not strong enough.

40
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:46,083
I can't do it.

41
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:48,375
[gasps]

42
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:51,500
That's why you want me to go.

43
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:55,916
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yes.
-I'll live, if I run now?

44
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,041
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes.

45
00:04:05,375 --> 00:04:06,750
Okay.

46
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,541
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] You've decided?
-[COWGIRL] Yeah.

47
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:12,708
[sighs]

48
00:04:12,791 --> 00:04:15,750
I'm sorry,
but I'm not going to run away,

49
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:19,083
because you're going
to stay behind. Right?

50
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:24,416
You always do that,
go silent when you're at a loss.

51
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:27,000
It's cute.
[chuckles]

52
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:34,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
They won't just kill you.

53
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:36,958
Yes. I know that.

54
00:04:37,041 --> 00:04:39,458
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I've seen it, what they do.

55
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:41,333
Yes.

56
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:43,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Don't think that you'll survive.

57
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:47,500
Yes, you might live,
but you'll be dead inside.

58
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:49,000
♪

59
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:50,958
So you need to run!

60
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:53,041
[COWGIRL]
I told you, I'm staying!

61
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:57,041
I can't...

62
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:59,375
I can't go through that again!

63
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:03,000
I won't just run away

64
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:06,333
knowing you're going to lose
your home a second time.

65
00:05:06,416 --> 00:05:08,750
And, besides,

66
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,666
maybe we'd escape,

67
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:13,500
but the farm,
it'd be completely destroyed.

68
00:05:13,583 --> 00:05:17,875
Even if we came back,
well, there would be nothing.

69
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:20,041
You know?

70
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:24,708
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] I see.
-Yeah. I really am sorry.

71
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:27,291
I know I'm being stubborn,

72
00:05:27,375 --> 00:05:29,875
not to mention foolish.

73
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:35,500
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Don't look at me like that.

74
00:05:35,583 --> 00:05:37,583
[whimpering]

75
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:42,083
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I'll do everything I can.

76
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:44,750
-Everything.
-Okay!

77
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:47,291
[sobbing]

78
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:54,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
"You have to protect those

79
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:56,291
who are smaller than you."

80
00:05:57,666 --> 00:05:59,708
[UNCLE]
Hey.

81
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:01,833
You ought to at least say
goodbye when you're leaving.

82
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:04,916
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
You're right. I'm sorry.

83
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,083
[UNCLE]
She's a good girl, you know?

84
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:12,916
Despite everything,
she's grown up so well.

85
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,166
Keep her safe. You got it?

86
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I'll try my best, sir.

87
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:28,583
[UNCLE] Sometimes I wish
you would just lie.

88
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,083
[doors creak]

89
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:33,291
-[VILLAGERS chattering]
-[GUILD GIRL gasps]

90
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:36,625
Uh...

91
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:40,208
Well, look who it is.

92
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:43,500
Figured you'd crawled off
and died somewhere.

93
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:45,250
You just gonna
stand there or what?

94
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:46,666
[ARCHER]
Huh?

95
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:50,166
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I apologize, but hear me out.

96
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,666
I have a request.

97
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,666
The Goblin Slayer has a request?

98
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,583
Isn't he a solo
adventurer, though?

99
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,791
[ADVENTURER] Nah. I hear
he's been going out on quests

100
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,000
-with a party lately.
-Really, him?

101
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:02,500
[GOBLIN SLAYER] A horde of
goblins has been scouting a farm

102
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:04,416
on the outskirts of town.

103
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,166
I don't know
how many there are,

104
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:07,791
but they'll probably
attack tonight.

105
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:10,583
Something about goblins.
Big surprise, huh?

106
00:07:10,666 --> 00:07:12,541
[ADVENTURER] What's the big deal
about a horde of goblins?

107
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:15,083
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Judging by
the footprints the scouts left,

108
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,791
they're led by a Goblin Lord,

109
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:19,000
which means there's at least
a hundred of them.

110
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:20,708
-[SPEARMAN gasping]
-[GUILDSMAN A] A hundred?

111
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:23,041
-That many?
-He's gotta be kidding.

112
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:25,500
-[GUILDSMAN B] There's no way.
-[GUILDSMAN C] It's impossible.

113
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:27,916
[GUILDSMAN D]
What's going on?

114
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,208
-You lost, too?
-Yeah.

115
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:32,875
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Lords are
a mutated class of goblins

116
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:34,500
that excel in leadership.

117
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:37,375
-Think of them as the top rank.
-That sounds bad.

118
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
And the horde that it's leading

119
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:40,208
will be here soon.

120
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:41,541
There's no time.

121
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:43,666
I could handle them in a cave,

122
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:46,125
but I can't kill them
out in the open, alone.

123
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:52,375
Please,
I'm asking for your help.

124
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:55,583
[VILLAGERS murmuring]

125
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:57,791
-What should we do?
-Don't know.

126
00:07:57,875 --> 00:08:00,000
-What do you think?
-Some goblins need killing.

127
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,166
That's his thing,
so he should do it.

128
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,833
[GUILDSMAN]
You can count me out.

129
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:06,416
[GUILDSWOMAN] I'm not going near
those disgusting creatures.

130
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:07,875
[grunts, growls]

131
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,375
[SPEARMAN]
Hey!

132
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,958
Listen. I don't think you
understand how this works.

133
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:17,000
This guild hall
is for adventurers,

134
00:08:17,083 --> 00:08:19,666
and everyone here falls
under that banner.

135
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:22,166
Which means we don't
do anything as a favor.

136
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:25,333
So put up a quest
and offer up a reward.

137
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:26,666
-That right?

138
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,125
-[GUILD MEMBERS] Yeah!
-[GUILDSMAN A] Yeah!

139
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,583
[GUILDSMAN B]
We're adventurers!

140
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,791
[gasps] What the hell is wrong
with these people?

141
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:33,916
[SHAMAN]
Simmer down, Long-ears.

142
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,416
No need to stir the pot
and complicate things.

143
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,041
I understand
this boils your blood,

144
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,416
-but don't act rashly.
-Let me go!

145
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,583
[gasps]

146
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes, you're right.

147
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,458
So, what are you offering?

148
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:50,583
What's the elimination
of 100 goblins worth to you?

149
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,958
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Everything.
-Uh?

150
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:58,000
[GOBLIN SLAYER] I'll offer
everything I have as a reward.

151
00:08:58,083 --> 00:09:00,208
[SPEARMAN]
And what does that entail?

152
00:09:00,291 --> 00:09:01,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
All of my belongings,

153
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,958
and everything
within my discretion.

154
00:09:04,041 --> 00:09:08,041
My equipment, my assets,
my knowledge, my time, and--

155
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,750
Even your life?

156
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes, if that's what's necessary.

157
00:09:12,708 --> 00:09:15,375
And would you take your life
if I asked that of you?

158
00:09:15,458 --> 00:09:17,041
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
No. I can't do that.

159
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:18,583
Why?

160
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:20,333
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Because if I did,

161
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:22,916
it would hurt someone important.

162
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,583
I was told I can't let
that happen.

163
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:29,541
So I suppose, my life isn't
within my discretion.

164
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:31,208
[groans, sighs]

165
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:33,958
[SPEARMAN] I really have no clue
what's going on

166
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:36,500
under that beat-up old
helmet of yours,

167
00:09:36,583 --> 00:09:38,916
but it's fairly obvious
you're serious about this.

168
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes, extremely serious.

169
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,791
Well, damn it all to hell.

170
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:45,958
[chuckles]

171
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:51,500
I wouldn't ask you to off
yourself anyway, you dimwit.

172
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:53,500
A strong drink will suffice!

173
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:56,958
Come on, that's an amazing deal.

174
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:59,041
A man of my prestige agreed

175
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:01,666
to slay no small number
of goblins for you!

176
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,625
Where's your gratitude?

177
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:06,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Of course. Forgive me.

178
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:10,083
-Thank you.
-Uh... All right, that's enough.

179
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:12,583
Just thank me after
we've tallied up our kills.

180
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:14,208
-[ARCHER] I'm in!
-[CROWD gasping]

181
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:16,208
I'll slay some goblins
with you, gladly!

182
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:19,750
But I'm asking for something
in return from you as well.

183
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:21,250
Once all this is over,

184
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:23,250
promise that you'll come
with us on a real adventure!

185
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:25,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I swear it.

186
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,208
[SHAMAN]
My price is a bit steeper

187
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,083
than just one drink,
Beard-cutter.

188
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:31,166
I'm going to need
a whole barrel!

189
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:33,000
[GOBLIN SLAYER] All right.
Then you'll have it.

190
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:35,041
I'd also like to join
our elven friend

191
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:37,083
on this grand adventure,
if you'll have me.

192
00:10:37,166 --> 00:10:39,708
I wouldn't dream of going
without my party.

193
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,166
By that logic,
I can assume

194
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,791
I shall also be included
in your numbers.

195
00:10:43,875 --> 00:10:46,291
Though I don't mind
helping out a comrade in need,

196
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:48,833
if I were to ask for some
small token of reward...

197
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:50,375
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Cheese?

198
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:52,666
That, and one more item
would be appropriate.

199
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:56,416
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Ice cream?
-Oh! That's perfect.

200
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,791
A reward even
the gods would envy.

201
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:00,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
They don't belong to me,

202
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:03,583
but they are made at the farm.

203
00:11:03,666 --> 00:11:06,041
If wiping out the subterranean
scourge would also protect

204
00:11:06,125 --> 00:11:08,583
that exquisite ambrosia,
count me in.

205
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:11,500
Well now, that makes five--

206
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:14,166
[WITCH]
There were five. I'll be six.

207
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,500
Brilliant Inflammarae.

208
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:20,083
Seems your flame
has drawn more moths to it,

209
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:22,375
but will they burn their wings?

210
00:11:22,458 --> 00:11:24,375
[GUILD GIRL panting]
Listen up, everyone!

211
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:25,791
I have an announcement!

212
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:27,791
The guild's offering
a quest as well!

213
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:30,291
There is now a reward
of one gold coin

214
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:31,958
for every goblin slain!

215
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:34,666
-How's that for incentive?
-[GUILDSMAN A] Seriously?

216
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:36,291
[GUILDSMAN B]
A gold coin for every goblin?

217
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:37,541
That's great!

218
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,125
[MANAGER]
You're sure we can do this?

219
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:41,208
[CHIEF] Well, it is based
on intel from a silver rank,

220
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:43,000
so it's not a problem.

221
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:44,416
And besides,

222
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,541
with that kind of passion,
how could we say no?

223
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:47,875
Just keep an accurate count.

224
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:51,375
[sighs]
Suppose I've got no choice.

225
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:53,041
You're going too?

226
00:11:53,125 --> 00:11:55,333
It's not like I'm doing a favor
for Goblin Slayer, mind you,

227
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:57,625
but denying the reward
would be foolish.

228
00:11:57,708 --> 00:11:59,875
Really?
There's no need to lie about it.

229
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:01,333
I know the reason.

230
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:03,333
You're doing this
because he was the one

231
00:12:03,416 --> 00:12:05,916
who slayed the goblins
that attacked your hometown.

232
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,416
[groans]
Damn it! That's not so.

233
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,458
I'm doing this strictly to gain
some gold coins

234
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:11,791
and nothing more!

235
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:13,875
It furthers my goal
of becoming a Paladin.

236
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:16,708
I can't refuse anyone
in need of help.

237
00:12:16,791 --> 00:12:18,958
You hear that? If they're going
to join the fight,

238
00:12:19,041 --> 00:12:21,208
-then I guess I am as well.
-And I'm going too.

239
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:23,000
Looks like we're all
in this together, then.

240
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,916
-So, uh...
-What's wrong?

241
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,500
Just that I haven't ever slain
any goblins before.

242
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:31,208
Well, it is pretty dangerous.

243
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:33,666
But I'm thinking that now would
be the perfect time to start.

244
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:36,583
You're right.
We do owe him after all.

245
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:39,750
[ADVENTURER] Okay. We became
adventurers at the same time,

246
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:41,583
so it seems fate
has decided for me.

247
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:43,666
[GUILDSMAN] To be honest,
I think I'd actually miss

248
00:12:43,750 --> 00:12:45,250
all his talk
about goblins around here.

249
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,708
[GUILDSMAN B]
Yeah, the truth is,

250
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:48,333
he's really pretty popular
in the ol' guild hall.

251
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:50,250
[GUILDSMAN B] The one thing
worse than having him around

252
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,791
would be if he wasn't here
to drive us crazy.

253
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:53,500
I gotta say,

254
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:56,041
a quest this bizarre is way too
interesting for me to resist.

255
00:12:56,125 --> 00:12:57,583
That's great!

256
00:12:57,666 --> 00:13:00,083
Even though we're not
in your party or close friends,

257
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:01,916
we're all adventurers.

258
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,500
It's what we live for!

259
00:13:03,583 --> 00:13:06,000
[ALL]
The adventurers will handle it!

260
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:07,458
[cheering]

261
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:09,416
You don't need to fill out
any paperwork right now,

262
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,583
just give us the tally
when you return.

263
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:12,708
[giggles]

264
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:17,875
-Wonderful, isn't it?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yeah.

265
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:20,208
You realize, I'll be coming
with you too, right?

266
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:21,958
[GOBLIN SLAYER chuckles]
Yeah.

267
00:13:24,916 --> 00:13:26,916
[crickets chirring]

268
00:13:29,083 --> 00:13:31,083
♪

269
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,666
[growling, grunting]

270
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:45,958
-[chattering excitedly]
-[low growling]

271
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:53,208
[GOBLINS growling]

272
00:13:56,333 --> 00:13:59,625
[growling, roaring]

273
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,500
[GOBLIN LORD bellows]

274
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:07,125
[GOBLINS cheering]

275
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:08,916
[roars]

276
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:14,083
[growling]

277
00:14:16,583 --> 00:14:19,666
♪

278
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:21,208
[canary twittering]

279
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:26,500
[DRUID]
Everything will be fine.

280
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:30,250
I needed to hear that.

281
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,500
-[squawking]
-Huh? Over there!

282
00:14:32,583 --> 00:14:35,291
-[birds fluttering, squawking]
-[animals screeching]

283
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:38,708
[ADVENTURERS growling]

284
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:41,541
-[plants rustling]
-[GOBLINS muttering]

285
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,208
I hope you're ready for this.

286
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:50,583
[gasps, grunts]

287
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:55,541
[GOBLINS cackling]

288
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:01,250
[shuddering]

289
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:04,791
[growling, cackling]

290
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,583
[growling]

291
00:15:10,166 --> 00:15:11,625
[cackling]

292
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:12,500
[gasps]

293
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:14,583
[bodies thudding]

294
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,750
[warbling]

295
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:22,458
-Fall into Stupor.
-Go to sleep.

296
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:26,000
[SHAMAN]
Sleep, you filthy goblins!

297
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:27,958
[ADVENTURER]
Now!

298
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:29,833
Don't bother with the goblins!

299
00:15:29,916 --> 00:15:31,333
[GOBLINS gasping]

300
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:34,166
Just grab the captives
and get 'em outta here!

301
00:15:34,250 --> 00:15:36,583
Hurry! Fall back! Now!

302
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:43,583
[ARCHER] Using human shields?
Despicable.

303
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:45,541
They deserve
every arrow they get.

304
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:48,375
[grunting]

305
00:15:48,458 --> 00:15:50,208
We've brought
all the women to safety!

306
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:52,625
[ARCHER] I've taken care of all
the spell-casters within sight.

307
00:15:52,708 --> 00:15:53,916
[GUILDSMAN]
Good work!

308
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,750
[lantern clattering]

309
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:57,833
[voices murmuring]

310
00:16:00,791 --> 00:16:02,333
Yeah! Now!

311
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:05,333
Time to earn your gold, boys!

312
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:08,708
-Attack!
-[ADVENTURERS shouting]

313
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:19,541
I look at these goblins,
and all I see is an easy payday!

314
00:16:19,625 --> 00:16:21,208
[grunting]

315
00:16:21,291 --> 00:16:24,041
[SPEARMAN] Damn! I can hardly
believe how many there are!

316
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:26,250
[grunting]

317
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:28,000
A real pain in the ass.

318
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,625
This is why even Goblin Slayer
couldn't do it on his own!

319
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:36,000
[blades slicing]

320
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,583
We knew it wouldn't be easy.

321
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:39,875
That definitely got
my juices flowin'!

322
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:45,208
[BOTH]
Huh?

323
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:46,125
[BOTH scream]

324
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:52,000
I'm sure you'd be fine
out on your own,

325
00:16:52,083 --> 00:16:53,916
but if you're close, I can use

326
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,166
-my Deflect Missiles spell.
-Hmm.

327
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:00,875
[growling]

328
00:17:00,958 --> 00:17:02,416
[distant screaming]

329
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,875
[LIGHT SWORDSMAN]
They're pushing hard.

330
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,666
Yeah. I should've gone
out there with them.

331
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,500
Wait. Do you see that?

332
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:13,625
[wolves growling]

333
00:17:13,708 --> 00:17:16,958
Those are the goblin riders,
just like he said.

334
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:17,875
[inhales]

335
00:17:17,958 --> 00:17:19,875
[whistling]

336
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,625
On guard! That means
the riders are coming!

337
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:22,875
Get ready!

338
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,708
[grunts]

339
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:27,083
All right everybody,
you know what to do!

340
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:29,500
Remember, we're going to need
to form two lines,

341
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:32,125
with the men in the back
filling the gaps in the front.

342
00:17:32,208 --> 00:17:33,958
Have your weapons out
and stay alert!

343
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:37,000
They're coming in low, so draw
them in as close as you can!

344
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,375
-Not yet!
-[growls]

345
00:17:40,458 --> 00:17:41,500
[SPEARMAN]
Keep waiting!

346
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:43,875
[wolves growling]

347
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:45,125
Get ready!

348
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,625
Here we go!

349
00:17:46,708 --> 00:17:50,041
[shouting]

350
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:51,250
[growls]

351
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,958
♪

352
00:17:59,250 --> 00:18:00,958
[ADVENTURERS groaning]

353
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:05,541
Back-line troops!
Let's move in!

354
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:07,625
[shouting]

355
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,625
There. Here it comes.

356
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:17,541
[gasps]

357
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,208
Oh. It's dead.

358
00:18:21,291 --> 00:18:22,500
[sighs]

359
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:23,500
-[blade clanks]
-[grunts]

360
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:27,583
Ha-yah!

361
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:29,958
Get your head out of the clouds
and into the fight!

362
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:31,791
You want your gold, don't ya?

363
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:33,333
[gasps]

364
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:34,875
[APPRENTICE CLERIC]
Are you hurt?

365
00:18:34,958 --> 00:18:36,333
No.

366
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,625
My armor saved me.
Thank God.

367
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,041
[HEAVY SWORDSMAN]
Pretty easy money, huh?

368
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:45,000
Yeah, but without his strategy,

369
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:47,666
you might be singing
a very different tune right now.

370
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:49,333
[HEAVY SWORDSMAN scoffs]

371
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:53,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Set ambushes.
It's a tool they use often,

372
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,958
but they won't
expect it from others.

373
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:57,375
They'll be leading
with meat shields.

374
00:18:57,458 --> 00:19:00,125
We'll cast sleeping spells
and when they fall,

375
00:19:00,208 --> 00:19:02,166
that's when we rescue
the hostages.

376
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,708
Just leave the sleeping
goblins on the ground.

377
00:19:04,791 --> 00:19:06,666
We don't want them to wake up.

378
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:09,875
A bigger horde like this will
have riders on trained wolves.

379
00:19:09,958 --> 00:19:12,833
There'll probably be
20 or 30 of them.

380
00:19:12,916 --> 00:19:15,375
We can take most of them
out with spear walls.

381
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:17,125
Those of us
not holding up the wall

382
00:19:17,208 --> 00:19:19,083
will kill the survivors.

383
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:21,958
You can use weapons or spells,
whatever it takes.

384
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,833
We'll need to kill
their spell-casters

385
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:25,458
as soon as possible.

386
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:27,458
[GOBLIN LORD shouts orders]

387
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:32,125
[roaring]

388
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:34,125
Underneath all that
tarnished metal,

389
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:36,083
there really is a silver rank.

390
00:19:37,583 --> 00:19:39,416
You went and ran too
far away from the group,

391
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,083
you stupid goblin!

392
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:43,166
-[screaming]
-[chuckling]

393
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,958
Hey, find any stragglers
over there--

394
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:49,000
[whimpering]

395
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:52,458
-[screaming]
-What was that?

396
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:54,625
Something's flying this way,
watch your heads!

397
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:55,916
[BOTH gasp]

398
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:59,166
-[thuds, squelches]
-[gasps]

399
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:02,333
[gasps]

400
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:05,083
[pounding footsteps]

401
00:20:05,166 --> 00:20:06,083
[GREENHORN WARRIOR screams]

402
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:08,166
[growling]

403
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,333
[growls]

404
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,333
Looks like we've got some hobs!

405
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:13,750
-[HEAVY SWORDSMAN] No.
-[SOLDIERS gasp]

406
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:16,458
[HEAVY SWORDSMAN]
That's a big boy.

407
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:21,041
A goblin champion.

408
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:23,416
[SPEARMAN]
Make that two of 'em.

409
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:26,666
[roars]

410
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,166
[HEAVY SWORDSMAN]
Nice.

411
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:31,125
I was getting a little bored
with all the small-frys.

412
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:34,041
I may actually break a sweat
taking these guys down.

413
00:20:34,125 --> 00:20:36,708
Are you asking for help?
I don't know, how can I fight,

414
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:38,250
and count up
all these goblin heads

415
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:41,250
-I've collected so far?
-I'm sure you'll find the time.

416
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:44,750
-Step back, okay?
-[WITCH] As you wish.

417
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:46,291
Those heads look heavy.

418
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:48,125
We may actually be
doing the beasts a favor

419
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,666
by taking them
off their shoulders.

420
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,416
This has turned into
a veteran's battlefield.

421
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:55,083
If you doubt your skills,
get out of the way!

422
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:56,958
[blades tinging]

423
00:20:57,041 --> 00:20:59,791
-[roaring]
-[shouting]

424
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:06,708
Crazy.

425
00:21:06,791 --> 00:21:08,791
[WITCH]
May I have some water?

426
00:21:08,875 --> 00:21:11,791
-Yes, right away.
-Thank you, dear.

427
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:13,125
Are you sure
that they don't need you

428
00:21:13,208 --> 00:21:15,166
out there on the battlefield?

429
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:19,166
[WITCH] I am,
to be quite honest.

430
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:23,083
He's far more used
to dispatching these brutes

431
00:21:23,166 --> 00:21:26,041
-than normal goblins.
-Wait a sec.

432
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:28,958
Does anybody know where Goblin
Slayer might have run off to?

433
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:34,000
Of course. Think,
ask yourself who he is.

434
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:35,708
[ARCHER]
Yes.

435
00:21:35,791 --> 00:21:37,291
It's not that tough
to figure out.

436
00:21:40,708 --> 00:21:43,541
[GOBLIN LORD panting]

437
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,333
[growls]

438
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:59,250
[ARCHER] Obviously,
he went to slay some goblins.

439
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,333
[growls]

440
00:23:42,458 --> 00:23:44,125
[dice clatter]

